This is an all ages, untimed bike ride. Riders are expected to follow and obey all traffic laws. The out and back ride will start at the Kettering Recreation Center, continue onto the streets of the City of Kettering, join the Iron Horse Bike Path and then the Creekside Trail. Riders will turn around in Beavercreek at 5th 3rd Park and ride back the same way they came out. The planned route is 15­-miles, but riders can turn around at anytime. Riders may continue past the turn around ride longer;this is done at the rider’s discretion and is not supported. All riders must have completed ride courses by 8:30pm. There will be snacks and drinks at the turn around; restrooms are available at the turn around at 5th 3rd Park in Beavercreek. All turns will be marked with cones and signs, please review the course in advance.
notes: This is a fun ride; it is not a race. All ages are welcome.
directions: Registration, and the Start and Finish Lines will be at the Kettering Recreation Center Complex, 2900 Glengarry Dr, Kettering, OH 45420.

Buckeye Cyclesport Beginner Race Clinic
description:
Buckeye Cyclesport will present a series of 3 beginner racing clinics, starting June 21.  These clinics are intended for riders just getting started in USA Cycling massed start road racing.

Clinics will focus on:

    Safety and protecting your bike in a group
    Advanced paceline skills
    Moving around in a group
    Attacking, and marking attacks
    Finishing
    Climbing

Clinics will be on 3 consecutive Tuesday nights.  Each clinic will last approximately 2 hours.

Clinics are intended for riders 16 years and older, with some basic group riding experience, who can comfortably maintain an 18-20mph pace with a group.

Events are USA Cycling permitted and insured.  Cost will be $15 per clinic, or $30 for all 3 clinics.  For insurance purposes USA Cycling annual or 1 day license is required.
course: Clinic will be run in parking lots, bike paths, and back roads as appropriate for the drills being covered

title: Cap City Short Track Finale
description: Cap City Collective's, co-founder, Spencer Hackett has been hosting, organizing and running the Cap City Short Track Mountain Bike Series since 2012. Initially, the series took place at Darree Fields in Dublin, OH, but as it grew in size a more suitable venue was needed. Building on the Cap City Cross series Spencer and the two other Cap City Collective founders negotiated with the city to allow the series to move to Big Run Park. From humble beginnings, the lighthearted, fun series has grown into a 60 participant mid-week racing event design to help usher in the transition from road to cyclocross season.
course: The course will feature the Chestnut Ridge grass loop, brief single track section and technical MTB features.
notes: This is a fundraiser event for COMBO (Central Ohio Mountain Bike Association) and will facilitate the growth of short track racing in central Ohio through the beginnings of a partnership between Cap City Collective and COMBO.
directions:
Chestnut Ridge Mountain Bike Trail
5260 Mason Road, Carroll, OH

title: Ohio Interscholastic League Race #3 - Reagan Park XC
Columbus Cyclocross Practice Series
description:
Join Cap City Collective and the Columbus cyclocross community for another year of cyclocross practices! This year the practices will remain at Cap City Collective's home base, Big Run Park's Derby Hill. This practice is appropriate for riders of all levels, from "I've never ridden a bike on the dirt before" to "I podium at Cincy3."

    Helmets and a functional bike (Cyclocross or MTB) are required.
    Water & food are not available on site, so please come prepared.
    Gloves and glasses are recommended.

The venue will be open from 5pm until dark, with organized instruction beginning at 6pm. The series runs every Tuesday evening starting the first Tuesday in September until the last Tuesday in October.

Tentative Practice schedule:

    Week 1 - Barriers & Introduction to Cyclocross
    Week 2 - Cornering & Starts
    Week 3 - Climbing & Off Cambers
    Week 4-8 will begin the mock races.
        We will have a short course arranged with flags or tape to simulate situations you will encounter in real races.
        A, B, & C groups will each have 2-3 chances to race throughout the night.
        New or inexperienced riders will be able to participate in breakout sessions to work on specific skills independent of the racing.

About The Donations & Cost

In the past cyclocross practices in Columbus have been free. These practices were uninsured and not permitted. To use Big Run Park and to take advantage of the insurance provided by USA Cycling Cap City Collective is required to cover the fees associated with the USA Cycling Permit, the City of Columbus park permit, and a per-rider insurance fee. Your donations will go directly to covering these costs. Any profits will be directly contributed to future off-road development programming through Cap City Collective. A $35 donation will cover the per-rider insurance fees for one rider and a portion of the permitting fees for the event. You are encouraged to donate more than $35 to cover other riders or future programming.

notes:
Fast, rolling terrain with off cambers, paved, the monstrous derby hill, grass climbing, and wide open turns.

Presented by Paradise Garage Racing

Race more!
After registering for one race the cost of each additional race on the same day is only $10.00. This discount will be automatically applied when registering for multiple races. 

There is no extra fee for day of race registration.

Callups & CX Cup Info:

    We will be doing call-ups based on CrossResults.com points for ALL pre-registered riders. Day of registered riders will be staged in order of registration. Pre-register for you best call-up!

Kids Race: 

The kid's race is FREE, sweets, treats and more for all that enter! Kids will have a separate, smaller circuit course located near the start/finish. The kids race will begin at 1:30, but the kid's course will be open all day for riding. 

 

Numbers & Fine Print

Please remember to bring your series number. Numbers will be re-issued for $10.

All results will be submitted to USAC within 48 hours after the official results are final.

The promoter and / or officials reserve the right to lengthen, shorten, modify, combine or cancel races and or prize list as a result of insufficient entries, inclement weather, dangerous conditions, statutes and laws, emergencies, and or race conditions.

Race day registration begins at 8:30am and closes approximately 15 minutes before each race

    This race is held under USA Cycling rules.  All racers must have a valid USAC license.
    One day USAC licenses (Men Cat 5 & Women Cat 4 only, One-day licenses may also be used for "Open" category races like Masters and SS if you are Men Category 5 or Women Category 4 - all other categories in the "Open" race will be required to have an annual USAC license) will be available for $10.00.
